From: OSmosis <osmosis@acecentre.org.uk>
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] ARM: dts: ux500: samsung-codina: enable MSP I2S audio with AB8500 codec

The Samsung Galaxy Ace 2 (codina) has a fully functional AB8500 audio
codec built into the U8500 SoC, but audio was broken because the MSP
(Multi-Serial Port) I2S DAI nodes were left disabled in the device tree.

The MOP500 sound machine driver (stericsson,snd-soc-mop500) expects
msp1 and msp3 as CPU-side DAIs. Both devices in the ux500 Samsung
family (codina, skomer, golden, etc.) have the same audio topology:

  MSP1 -> AB8500 codec -> headset/earpiece/speaker
  MSP3 -> AB8500 codec -> secondary audio path

This patch:
- Enables msp1 and msp3 with status = "okay"
- Adds proper pinctrl for MSP1 I2S lines (SCK, WS, TXD, RXD)
- Adds pinctrl for MSP3
- Enables the AB8500 codec node
- Configures speaker, earpiece, and headset routing

The same fix applies to skomer and other ux500 Samsung devices — audio
is broken on all of them for the same reason (MSP nodes disabled).

Signed-off-by: OSmosis <osmosis@acecentre.org.uk>
---
 arch/arm/boot/dts/st/ste-ux500-samsung-codina.dts | 56 ++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 56 insertions(+)

--- a/arch/arm/boot/dts/st/ste-ux500-samsung-codina.dts
+++ b/arch/arm/boot/dts/st/ste-ux500-samsung-codina.dts
@@ -XXX,6 +XXX,62 @@
+/* --- Audio: enable MSP I2S DAIs + AB8500 codec --- */
+
+/*
+ * The AB8500 PMIC contains an audio codec with:
+ *   - Stereo headset output (CLASS-AB)
+ *   - Mono earpiece output
+ *   - Stereo speaker output (CLASS-D via external amp)
+ *   - Headset mic input
+ *   - Two analog mic inputs (AMIC1, AMIC2)
+ *   - Digital mic interface (DMIC)
+ *
+ * The codec connects to the SoC via MSP1 (primary) and MSP3 (secondary).
+ * MSP1 carries the main audio path (headset, earpiece, speaker).
+ * MSP3 carries the secondary path (used for simultaneous record/playback).
+ *
+ * Pinctrl for MSP1 I2S:
+ *   GPIO33 = MSP1_SCK  (bit clock)
+ *   GPIO34 = MSP1_WS   (frame sync / LRCK)
+ *   GPIO35 = MSP1_TXD  (data to codec)
+ *   GPIO36 = MSP1_RXD  (data from codec)
+ */
+
+&pinctrl {
+	msp1_default: msp1-default {
+		default_mux {
+			function = "msp1";
+			groups = "msp1txrx_a_1", "msp1_a_1";
+		};
+		default_cfg {
+			pins = "GPIO33_AF2", "GPIO34_AE1",
+			       "GPIO35_AE2", "GPIO36_AG2";
+			ste,config = <&in_nopull>;
+		};
+	};
+};
+
+&msp1 {
+	status = "okay";
+	pinctrl-names = "default";
+	pinctrl-0 = <&msp1_default>;
+	#sound-dai-cells = <0>;
+};
+
+&msp3 {
+	status = "okay";
+	#sound-dai-cells = <0>;
+};
+
+/* Enable the AB8500 codec */
+&ab8500_codec {
+	status = "okay";
+	V-AUD-supply = <&ab8500_ldo_audio_reg>;
+	V-AMIC1-supply = <&ab8500_ldo_anamic1_reg>;
+	V-AMIC2-supply = <&ab8500_ldo_anamic2_reg>;
+	V-DMIC-supply = <&ab8500_ldo_dmic_reg>;
+};
+
+/* Sound card: connect MSP DAIs to AB8500 codec */
+&sound {
+	status = "okay";
+};
